==============================================================================
PART 5: NAIVE FORMULA IN BINOMIAL BASIS
==============================================================================
g_k^naive(m) = sum_{r=1}^{k} C(k-1,r-1) * 2^{r-1} * C(m,r)
By construction, the binomial coefficient of C(m,r) is C(k-1,r-1)*2^{r-1}

k=1: naive coeffs [C(m,0), C(m,1), ..., C(m,1)] = [0, 1]
k=2: naive coeffs [C(m,0), C(m,1), ..., C(m,2)] = [0, 1, 2]
k=3: naive coeffs [C(m,0), C(m,1), ..., C(m,3)] = [0, 1, 4, 4]
k=4: naive coeffs [C(m,0), C(m,1), ..., C(m,4)] = [0, 1, 6, 12, 8]
k=5: naive coeffs [C(m,0), C(m,1), ..., C(m,5)] = [0, 1, 8, 24, 32, 16]
k=6: naive coeffs [C(m,0), C(m,1), ..., C(m,6)] = [0, 1, 10, 40, 80, 80, 32]
k=7: naive coeffs [C(m,0), C(m,1), ..., C(m,7)] = [0, 1, 12, 60, 160, 240, 192, 64]
k=8: naive coeffs [C(m,0), C(m,1), ..., C(m,8)] = [0, 1, 14, 84, 280, 560, 672, 448, 128]
k=9: naive coeffs [C(m,0), C(m,1), ..., C(m,9)] = [0, 1, 16, 112, 448, 1120, 1792, 1792, 1024, 256]


